		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yeah, you could use /RAM1CE as A15, and AND(/RAM1CE,/RAM2CE) as /BiggerRAMCE, if you could get your hands on a ≥64 KiB SRAM.<br /><br />But NES-ETROM is already nicely set up for this upgrade (SL15/CL15), and I'm pretty certain it'd be easier to piggy-back an extra RAM onto NES-EWROM.

		

		</td>
