	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: SimCity prototype found!</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />On ELROM, you could piggy-back a 32-pin 128Ki x 8 SRAM on top of (or underneath) the existing PRG-ROM, without <em>too</em> many random bonus wires... but it is an awful lot of fiddly rework, including a good deal of SMT work to get to the pins on the MMC5 that aren't broken out.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


